{{Glossary
|Entry=Construal
|Description=A construal is the process by which a person's experience in the world is conceived.  This construal relationship is one between the conceptualizer (usually the speaker or the addressee) and the conceptualization entertained (the linguistic utterance).
|Applies to=Metaphor & Frame
|Utility=General Theory
